It seems like a 3 on the AP Calc AB subscore of BC should be enough. You should probably talk with an advisor in person about the discrepancy.

Im currently a senior CS major and I thought I satisfied this with my AP scores (3 on AP Calc AB Subscore of BC) but on the academic report it still says this is missing. Does a 3 on AP Calc AB Subscore satisfy the requirement for Math 1A for the CS major? If not, I have taken basically every mathy ee/cs course and have done decently well so it would be great if this would be waived.
